@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container-fluid p-0">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <div class="feature-card text-center text-white d-flex flex-column justify-content-center align-items-center bg-primary-subtle position-relative rounded">
        <div class="position-relative text-center px-3" style="z-index: 2;">
            <h1 class="display-3 fw-bold text-uppercase">Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p class="lead mt-3">Your data matters. Here’s how we handle it responsibly.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Privacy Policy Section -->
    <div class="privacy-content-section">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="fw-bold mt-5 text-warning">Introduction</h2>
            <p>
                We, Web Technology Group-17, are committed to respecting and protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you interact with our services or platforms.
            </p>

            <h2 class="fw-bold mt-5 text-warning">1. Controllers of Personal Information</h2>
            <p>
                Web Technology Group-17, affiliated with SDU, oversees the management of personal data collected via our projects and platforms. Our headquarters are based at Alsion.
            </p>

            <h2 class="fw-bold mt-5 text-warning">2. What Personal Information We Collect</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Information you provide:</strong> Name, email address, academic details, and other voluntarily submitted data.</li>
                <li><strong>Automatically collected:</strong> Usage data, cookies, IP address, and device information.</li>
                <li><strong>Third-party sources:</strong> Data from external services like payment processors or analytics providers (if applicable).</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="fw-bold mt-5 text-warning">3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>To provide, maintain, and improve our services.</li>
                <li>To comply with institutional and legal requirements.</li>
                <li>For academic research and development purposes.</li>
                <li>For personalization and recommendations.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="fw-bold mt-5 text-warning">4. Cookies and Identifiers</h2>
            <p>
                Web Technology Group-17 uses cookies to enhance functionality and improve user experience. You can manage your preferences via your browser settings or through our cookie management tool.
            </p>

            <h2 class="fw-bold mt-5 text-warning">5. Data Sharing</h2>
            <p>
                We do not sell your data. We, Web Technology Group-17, share information only with trusted institutional partners or service providers under strict confidentiality agreements, where necessary.
            </p>

            <h2 class="fw-bold mt-5 text-warning">6. Your Rights</h2>
            <p>
                You have the right to access, update, or request the deletion of your personal data. For assistance, please contact our Project Lead at Alsion.
            </p>

            <h2 class="fw-bold mt-5 text-warning">7. Security Measures</h2>
            <p>
                We prioritize data security using encryption, secure servers, and strict access controls. Our protocols comply with institutional and industry standards.
            </p>

            <h2 class="fw-bold mt-5 text-warning">8. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>
                For privacy-related inquiries, please reach out to us at Alsion.
            </p>

            <h2 class="fw-bold mt-5 text-warning">9. Updates to This Policy</h2>
            <p>
                This policy may be updated periodically to reflect changes in our practices. Please revisit this page for the latest version.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
